class Solution {
    /**
    The Fib4 number sequence is a sequence similar t o  the Fibbonacci sequnece t hat'sdefined as foll o ws:
   fib4(0 ) -> 0
    f ib4(1)  -> 0
   fib4(2) -> 2
    fib4(3) ->  0
   fib4( n)  -> fib4(n-1) + fib4(n-2)  +fib4(n-3) + fib4(n-4).
    Pleas e write a function to efficiently compute the n-th element of the fib4 number sequ ence.  Do not use recursion.
    >>> fib4(5)
    4
    >>> fib4(6)
    8
    >>> fib4(7)
    14
     */
    public int fib4(int n) {
        if (n <= 1) return n;
        int f1 = fib4(n - 1);
        int f2 = fib4(n - 2);
        return f1 + f2 + f1 + f2;
    }
}

